{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"User-controlled swap params can spend arbitrary token balances held by gateway contracts","locations":["GatewayCrossChain.sol:373","GatewayCrossChain.sol:492","GatewayTransferNative.sol:414","GatewayTransferNative.sol:453","GatewayTransferNative.sol:574","GatewaySend.sol:199","GatewaySend.sol:245","GatewaySend.sol:366"],"claim":"The contracts decode `MixSwapParams` from attacker-controlled payloads and use `params.fromToken` / `params.fromTokenAmount` in approvals and `mixSwap` without enforcing that they match the token and net amount actually received in the current execution path.","impact":"Attackers can spend unrelated token balances already held by these contracts (fees, stranded balances, prior user funds) and route swap outputs to attacker-controlled recipients, causing direct theft.","paths":["Craft payload/swapData with `params.fromToken` set to a valuable token currently held by the contract and `params.fromTokenAmount` set to the desired drain amount.","Trigger `onCall`, `withdrawToNativeChain`, or `depositAndCall` with cheap/unrelated input.","Contract approves DODO for attacker-chosen token and `mixSwap` pulls/spends contract inventory for attacker benefit."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Refunds for non-20-byte recipients are claimable by anyone","locations":["GatewayCrossChain.sol:607","GatewayCrossChain.sol:612","GatewayTransferNative.sol:685","GatewayTransferNative.sol:689"],"claim":"In both `claimRefund` implementations, when `walletAddress.length != 20`, `receiver` remains `msg.sender`; the caller check then trivially passes for arbitrary callers.","impact":"Refunds intended for non-EVM recipients (e.g., Bitcoin/Solana-style addresses) can be front-run and stolen by any observer.","paths":["A failed cross-chain call stores refund info with non-20-byte `walletAddress`.","Attacker observes `externalId` and calls `claimRefund(externalId)` first.","Authorization passes trivially and funds are transferred to attacker."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Bitcoin/non-EVM revert recipient is truncated to 20 bytes, misdirecting refunds","locations":["GatewayCrossChain.sol:318","GatewayCrossChain.sol:550","GatewayTransferNative.sol:319","GatewayTransferNative.sol:631"],"claim":"`withdraw` encodes revert recipient as `bytes20(sender)`, truncating non-20-byte addresses. `onRevert` then interprets the 52-byte revert payload as an EVM address refund target.","impact":"Failed non-EVM withdrawals can refund to unintended EVM addresses (or unusable addresses), causing permanent user fund loss.","paths":["User initiates withdrawal with a non-20-byte recipient format.","Withdrawal fails and gateway calls `onRevert` with truncated 20-byte recipient bytes.","Contract refunds to that truncated EVM address instead of the intended non-EVM recipient."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"withdrawToNativeChain trusts nominal input amount and can execute underfunded withdrawals from contract reserves","locations":["GatewayTransferNative.sol:549","GatewayTransferNative.sol:554","GatewayTransferNative.sol:555","GatewayTransferNative.sol:570","GatewayTransferNative.sol:574","GatewayTransferNative.sol:577","GatewayTransferNative.sol:599","GatewayTransferNative.sol:477"],"claim":"`withdrawToNativeChain` uses caller-supplied `amount` as the accounting source for fee/swap/withdraw flows, but does not verify actual token balance delta. The ETH sentinel path skips transfer-in entirely, and ERC20 paths only check a boolean `transferFrom` return.","impact":"Attackers can trigger withdrawals of real `decoded.targetZRC20` from contract-held inventory without providing equivalent funding, enabling direct theft of pooled assets.","paths":["Call `withdrawToNativeChain(_ETH_ADDRESS_, amount, message)` to bypass token pull, then route to valuable `targetZRC20`.","Or use a malicious/deflationary token that returns success while transferring less than `amount`.","Contract computes output from nominal `amount` and executes gateway withdrawal using existing target-token balances."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"GatewaySend destination onCall trusts payload amount/token data and can drain contract reserves","locations":["GatewaySend.sol:347","GatewaySend.sol:354","GatewaySend.sol:359","GatewaySend.sol:363","GatewaySend.sol:370","GatewaySend.sol:372"],"claim":"`GatewaySend.onCall` trusts `amount`, `fromToken`, and `toToken` decoded from attacker-controlled payload bytes instead of reconciling to assets delivered by gateway for that call. The function can skip funding pulls (`fromToken == ETH sentinel`) and also ignores ERC20 transfer return values.","impact":"Crafted cross-chain payloads can force ETH/ERC20 payouts from pre-existing contract balances to attacker-controlled recipients, causing direct theft.","paths":["Send cross-chain call with payload encoding inflated `amount` and attacker-chosen token mode.","Destination `onCall` computes `outputAmount` from payload values, not reconciled balances.","Contract transfers ETH/ERC20 reserves to attacker recipient."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-006","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Reentrancy in `GatewayTransferNative.claimRefund` allows repeated refund claims","locations":["GatewayTransferNative.sol:691","GatewayTransferNative.sol:692"],"claim":"`claimRefund` performs external token transfer before deleting `refundInfos[externalId]`, enabling reentrancy on malicious refund tokens.","impact":"A malicious token can reenter and claim the same refund multiple times in one transaction, draining additional token balance held by the contract.","paths":["Create refund entry where `refundInfo.token` is a reentrant token.","Call `claimRefund(externalId)`; token transfer reenters before storage deletion.","Repeated claims execute until balance is exhausted or reentrancy stops."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-007","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Balance-based pair existence check can be dust-poisoned into swap-path DoS","locations":["GatewayCrossChain.sol:234","GatewayCrossChain.sol:245","GatewayTransferNative.sol:235","GatewayTransferNative.sol:246","libraries/UniswapV2Library.sol:44"],"claim":"`_existsPairPool` infers pair existence by token balances at computed pair address rather than verifying deployed pair code/reserves.","impact":"Attackers can dust non-pair addresses so routing selects nonexistent direct pools, causing reserve lookups/swaps to revert and denying service for affected routes.","paths":["For a token pair without a real direct pool, send dust of both tokens to computed pair address.","`_existsPairPool` returns true and route selection chooses 2-hop direct path.","Subsequent `getReserves`/swap calls revert on non-pair target, blocking those swaps."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-008","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Public `withdraw` can be abused when residual gateway allowances remain","locations":["GatewayTransferNative.sol:305","GatewayTransferNative.sol:319","GatewayTransferNative.sol:416","GatewayTransferNative.sol:477","GatewayTransferNative.sol:496"],"claim":"`GatewayTransferNative.withdraw` is publicly callable. Other flows approve `outputAmount + gasFee` when gas token equals output token, but gateway spends only `outputAmount`, leaving residual allowance under some conditions.","impact":"If residual approval and contract balance exist (notably after gas-fee changes), arbitrary callers may consume leftover allowance to trigger unauthorized withdrawals to attacker-chosen recipients.","paths":["A prior withdrawal path leaves nonzero residual allowance from `GatewayTransferNative` to gateway.","Attacker calls public `withdraw` with attacker-controlled recipient bytes and amount that fits remaining allowance conditions.","Gateway pulls contract tokens via leftover allowance and emits withdrawal to attacker destination."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-009","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Empty `swapDataZ` path allows cross-asset withdrawals without performing conversion","locations":["GatewayCrossChain.sol:369","GatewayCrossChain.sol:492","GatewayCrossChain.sol:495","GatewayCrossChain.sol:517","GatewayTransferNative.sol:449","GatewayTransferNative.sol:414","GatewayTransferNative.sol:574","GatewayTransferNative.sol:577","GatewayTransferNative.sol:599"],"claim":"When `swapDataZ` is empty, `_doMixSwap` returns the input `amount` directly. Callers can still set arbitrary `decoded.targetZRC20`, and withdrawal/payout logic proceeds as if a real conversion occurred.","impact":"Attackers can provide one asset but withdraw/receive a different, more valuable token from contract-held reserves, causing direct reserve theft.","paths":["Send message/call with `targetZRC20 != input zrc20` and empty `swapDataZ`.","`_doMixSwap` returns nominal input amount without any token conversion proof.","Contract executes withdraw/transfer in `targetZRC20` using its own inventory."],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-010","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"GatewaySend source flow does not bind bridged asset to swap output asset","locations":["GatewaySend.sol:245","GatewaySend.sol:257","GatewaySend.sol:266","GatewaySend.sol:170","GatewaySend.sol:186"],"claim":"`depositAndCall(fromToken,...)` computes a numeric `outputAmount` from `_doMixSwap`, then deposits whichever `asset` the caller supplied, without verifying that this asset was actually produced/received from the swap.","impact":"If the contract holds balances of another token/ETH, attackers can swap one asset but bridge out a different asset from pooled reserves.","paths":["Call `depositAndCall(fromToken, amount, swapData, ..., asset, ...)` with swap output token different from `asset`.","Obtain nonzero `outputAmount` (or force it via crafted swap data).","Contract deposits `outputAmount` of attacker-chosen `asset` to gateway, consuming contract reserves."],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-011","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"GatewayTransferNative refund records are overwriteable for the same externalId","locations":["GatewayTransferNative.sol:642","GatewayTransferNative.sol:648","GatewayTransferNative.sol:664","GatewayTransferNative.sol:670"],"claim":"`onRevert`/`onAbort` in `GatewayTransferNative` write `refundInfos[externalId]` without checking whether an entry already exists.","impact":"If duplicate/colliding callbacks occur for the same `externalId`, earlier refund metadata can be replaced, leading to refund loss, misdirection, or permanent unclaimability for the original claimant.","paths":["First callback stores refund info for `externalId = X`.","Second callback with same `X` stores different wallet/token/amount and overwrites prior data.","Original user can no longer claim intended refund entry."],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-012","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"AccountEncoder.decompressAccounts builds invalid memory layout for `Account[]`","locations":["libraries/AccountEncoder.sol:28","libraries/AccountEncoder.sol:33","libraries/AccountEncoder.sol:48","GatewayCrossChain.sol:425","GatewayCrossChain.sol:454","GatewayTransferNative.sol:505","GatewayTransferNative.sol:534"],"claim":"`decompressAccounts` stores pointers in array slots where static `Account` structs are expected inline, so later ABI encoding reads corrupted struct fields.","impact":"Solana-targeted payloads can be malformed and fail downstream decoding/calls, causing persistent route-level DoS/refund churn for affected transfers.","paths":["Use Solana path (`dstChainId == SOLANA_EDDY`) with compressed accounts data.","`decompressAccounts` produces malformed `Account[]` memory representation.","Encoded payload becomes invalid for downstream processing and withdraw-and-call fails."],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-013","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Recipient bytes are silently truncated/padded into EVM addresses in payout paths","locations":["GatewayTransferNative.sol:390","GatewaySend.sol:356"],"claim":"Both payout paths cast dynamic recipient bytes to `bytes20/address` without requiring exact 20-byte length.","impact":"Malformed or non-20-byte recipient payloads can be irreversibly misinterpreted, causing payouts to unintended EVM addresses and user fund loss.","paths":["Provide recipient bytes longer than 20 bytes with attacker-controlled first 20 bytes (or shorter bytes that get padded).","Contract truncates/pads and derives an EVM address without validation.","Funds are transferred to the derived address, not the intended recipient."],"round":2,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-014","severity":"High","confidence":"medium","title":"GatewaySend direct ERC20 source deposit uses nominal amount and can spend reserves on underfunded transfer-in","locations":["GatewaySend.sol:317","GatewaySend.sol:320","GatewaySend.sol:186"],"claim":"In `depositAndCall(address targetContract, uint256 amount, address asset, ...)`, ERC20 intake checks only `transferFrom` boolean success and never reconciles actual balance delta before approving/depositing the full nominal `amount` to the gateway.","impact":"With fee-on-transfer/deflationary ERC20s, the contract may receive less than `amount` but still bridge `amount`; any deficit is covered from pre-existing contract balances, enabling reserve drain and insolvency over repeated calls.","paths":["Call `depositAndCall(targetContract, amount, asset, ...)` using a taxed ERC20.","Contract receives `< amount` but still approves/deposits full `amount` to gateway.","Gateway pull succeeds using contract-held inventory to cover the shortfall, transferring value to attacker-controlled cross-chain flow."],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-015","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"GatewaySend destination finalizes success even when ERC20 payout transfer fails softly","locations":["GatewaySend.sol:372","GatewaySend.sol:385"],"claim":"`onCall` executes `IERC20(toToken).transfer(...)` without checking the returned boolean and then returns success to the gateway.","impact":"If a token returns `false` (instead of reverting), cross-chain delivery is marked successful while recipient payment never happens, causing silent non-delivery and potential fund lockup in the contract.","paths":["Process destination message where payout token's `transfer` returns `false`.","`onCall` does not revert and still returns success.","No revert/refund path is triggered, while recipient remains unpaid."],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-016","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"GatewaySend ETH payout uses `.transfer` and can DoS smart-contract recipients","locations":["GatewaySend.sol:370"],"claim":"ETH delivery uses Solidity `.transfer`, forwarding only 2300 gas to the recipient.","impact":"Many contract wallets/proxies cannot receive ETH under 2300 gas; affected cross-chain deliveries deterministically revert, reducing liveness for those recipients.","paths":["Set destination recipient to a contract with non-trivial `receive`/`fallback` logic.","`onCall` executes `payable(recipient).transfer(outputAmount)`.","Transfer reverts and delivery path fails for that recipient class."],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-017","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"GatewaySend revert handler lacks native-asset refund path and can strand reverted ETH","locations":["GatewaySend.sol:393","GatewaySend.sol:396"],"claim":"`onRevert` always calls ERC20-style `TransferHelper.safeTransfer(context.asset, ...)` and has no branch for native refunds. For gas-token reverts where `context.asset` is empty/zero-address, this call does not transfer ETH back to the user.","impact":"Failed ETH-origin cross-chain calls can be finalized without refunding the sender, leaving reverted value stranded in `GatewaySend` (and exposed to secondary reserve-drain bugs).","paths":["User submits ETH `depositAndCall` through `GatewaySend`.","Destination execution fails and gateway triggers `onRevert` with gas-token context.","Handler attempts token transfer using `context.asset` instead of native ETH transfer, so sender is not refunded."],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"GatewaySend destination `onCall` ignores `transferFrom` result and continues as if funds were received","source_agents":["codex_1"],"reason":"Duplicate of existing F-005, which already covers untrusted payload accounting plus ignored ERC20 transferFrom result in `GatewaySend.onCall`."},{"title":"Unbounded receiver bytes are persisted in refund records, enabling revert-callback gas exhaustion","source_agents":["codex_1"],"reason":"Not reportable as stated: upstream gateway enforces message/revert size caps, and no concrete protocol-wide gas-exhaustion path was substantiated."},{"title":"GatewayTransferNative exposes an ETH-sentinel path in `withdrawToNativeChain` that reverts at fee transfer","source_agents":["codex_1"],"reason":"Subset/variant of existing F-004 (underfunded sentinel path draining reserves); separate liveness framing is not distinct root cause."},{"title":"Missing deadline validation in GatewaySend swap execution","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`_doMixSwap` forwards deadline to DODO router, which is expected to enforce it; no independent deadline bypass was demonstrated in this code."},{"title":"No minimum output amount enforcement on source-chain swaps","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`minReturnAmount` is part of user-supplied swap params and enforced by the downstream swap; absence of extra wrapper checks is not a standalone vulnerability."},{"title":"Out-of-bounds calldata read in decodePackedMessage","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Malformed length fields cause a revert on that call path rather than exploitable memory corruption or cross-user fund impact."},{"title":"Predictable externalId enables front-running on source chains","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`externalId` is an identifier/event key, not an authorization primitive; predictability does not create direct theft or protocol manipulation by itself."},{"title":"Gas stipend limitation in refund ETH transfers","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Factually incorrect: `TransferHelper.safeTransferETH` uses `.call` without a 2300-gas stipend limit."},{"title":"Missing access control on GatewayTransferNative.withdraw function","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Already captured by existing F-008, where exploitability depends on residual gateway allowances and contract balances."},{"title":"Platform fee can be set to zero enabling free withdrawals","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Governance/owner-configurable economic parameter, not a security flaw in permissioning or accounting."},{"title":"Incorrect amountIn calculation in swap finalization","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The cited check is conservative and may only over-revert in edge cases; no realistic theft, insolvency, or permissionless DoS exploit was shown."}]}
